AMID a bad week in the life of Julius Malema, the most important woman in his life is in the intensive care unit of the Medi-Clinic heart hospital in Pretoria. Sarah Malema (82), his grandmother, was admitted about a week ago after a suspected heart attack. Malema has been visiting his grandmother regularly and was at the hospital yesterday, accompanied by four bodyguards. Mrs Malema’s condition has reportedly improved and she will soon be tranferred to a regular ward. — Own Correspondent.